{"key":"processedPost-6219430","value":{"id":6219430,"first":6218919,"last":6219430,"when":1162007508,"utime":"10/28/06 06:51 AM","content":"Bang the jars against a fully inflated car or bicycle tire to break up the grains into individual kernels so they can be simply poured out of the jar without touching them. Then, put a bit of coir in a tray, then pour a bit of grain, then a bit of coir, etc., until the tray is full.  I don't like to mix with hands or tools because sometimes it damages the kernels.  Broken kernels leave openings for contaminants.<br />RR","title":"Re: rye jars to coir.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}